{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17512273","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17512273"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T12:52:50+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T12:52:50+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11868"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"11868","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/11868"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.05,0.03,0.64,0.04,0.24]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4468"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"48363"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"4468","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4468"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11868"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"33277"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"23"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4340"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"6538"},{"type":"contributions","id":"6569"},{"type":"contributions","id":"13072"},{"type":"contributions","id":"14114"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"48363","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/48363"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 26-year-old woman has her initial review in the antenatal clinic. Her last menstrual period was 12/01/2022 and it is now 16/07/2022. Her periods are usually regular and her cycle length is 30 days. According to ultrasonography performed this morning, she is 26+0 weeks pregnant.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe following formula is based on 28-day cycles and can be used to calculate her estimated date of delivery (EDD):\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEDD = first day of LMP - 3 months + 1 year and 7 days\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is her most likely estimated due date?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["17/10/22","18/10/22","19/10/22","20/10/22","21/10/22"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EIn the first trimester of pregnancy, ultrasound examination is the most accurate assessment of gestational age. As the gestational age increases, as too does the margin of error of ultrasonography. \u003Cstrong\u003EAfter 24 weeks of pregnancy, LMP becomes the most reliable method of determining due date\u003C/strong\u003E.  Whilst usually this would be input into a date calculator online or automatically calculated on the patient\u0027s notes, it is important principles to learn. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn this case, her last menstrual period was 26 weeks ago, making the date of her LMP the more reliable method of determining EDD.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUsing the due date calculator supplied, her due date is 19/10/22. However, this calculation is based on a generic 28-day cycle. \u003Cstrong\u003EAny cycle length variation must be added or subtracted from the due date.\u003C/strong\u003E As this patient\u0027s cycle is 30 days, 2 days are added to the calculation and her estimated due date becomes 21/10/22.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Ultrasound measurement is the most reliable form of determining gestational age in the first trimester","When using LMP to calculate EDD, if a patients cycle length varies from 28 days, this variation must be added or subtracted from her due date."],"references":["Australian Government Department of Health and Aged Care.Pregnancy Care Guidelines, 20 Gestational age.2021","University hospitals.calculating a due date.2020"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemR